.TH BAUDZILLA485 1 "2025" "Baudzilla 1.0" "RS485 Test Tool"
.SH NAME
baudzilla485 \- RS485 bus test and protocol probe tool

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B baudzilla485
-p <port> -l <logfile> -s <string>
[-v] [-b <baud>] [-n <loops>] [-t <timeout>]
[--length <bytes>] [--pattern ascii|hex|random|walking|checker]
[--linecheck] [--modbus] [--iec101]
[--kernel] [--gpio <path>] [--manual-rts]

.SH DESCRIPTION
Baudzilla485 tests RS485 hardware in three modes:
kernel RS485 driver, GPIO controlled DE pin or manual RTS toggled DE.

Functions include loopback verification, idle line noise detection,
Modbus RTU probing and IEC101 probing.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B -v
Verbose mode.

.TP
.B -p <port>
Serial device (e.g. /dev/ttyS2).

.TP
.B -l <logfile>
Log file.

.TP
.B -s <string>
ASCII test string.

.TP
.B -b <baud>
Baudrate (default 9600).

.TP
.B -n <loops>
Loop count.

.TP
.B -t <timeout>
Timeout seconds.

.TP
.B --length <bytes>
Payload length.

.TP
.B --pattern <name>
Pattern mode: ascii hex random walking checker.

.TP
.B --linecheck
Detect idle line noise.

.TP
.B --modbus
Run Modbus RTU function 3 probe.

.TP
.B --iec101
Run IEC101 probe.

.TP
.B --kernel
Use kernel RS485 driver (default).

.TP
.B --gpio <path>
Use GPIO controlled DE pin.

.TP
.B --manual-rts
Use RTS as DE.

.TP
.B -h, --help
Show help.

.SH EXAMPLE
baudzilla485 -v -p /dev/ttyS2 -l out.txt -s "485" --manual-rts --modbus --iec101

